% ===================== SECTION 6 =====================
\section{Results and Discussion}
Selective participation substantially improves accuracy. Most alpha is generated during Risk-On regimes, while exposure is suppressed during hostile macro environments.

% ===================== SECTION 7 =====================
\section{Limitations}
The framework is evaluated on Bitcoin only, excludes transaction costs, and relies on lagged regime estimates.

% ===================== SECTION 8 =====================
\section{Conclusion}
We present a regime-aware meta-learning framework that prioritizes decision quality over unconditional prediction. The system demonstrates institutional realism, robustness across regimes, and strong empirical performance.

